<h1>@KJ{{location^fit}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li>@Vru{{}} <strong>@KJ{{location^fit}}@HI{{ha}}</strong>
<li>@Vta{{}} <strong>@KJ{{location^fit}}@HI{{ha}}</strong>
<li>@Vnai{{}} <strong>@KJ{{location^fit}}@HI{{ha}}</strong>
<li>@Ai{{}} <strong>@KJ{{location^fit}}@HI{{ha}}</strong>
<li>@Ana{{}} <strong>@KJ{{location^fit}}@HI{{ha}}</strong>
<li>@N{{}} @HI{{no}} <strong>@KJ{{location^fit}}@HI{{ha}}</strong>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<strong>@KJ{{location^fit}}</strong> is used to talk about a hypotheitcal situation; the subsequent
clause indicates how to cope with the situation or its consequences.
</br>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{meeting^deliberation}}ni @KJ{{interval}}ni@KJ{{fit}}wanai <strong>@KJ{{location^fit}}ha</strong>
      @KJ{{take*along^entwine}}shite kudasai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      If you cannot be in time for the meeting, please inform us.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

